\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latvia\"}, {\"begin\": 5263, \"end\": 5269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"score\": 0.9999996777578937, \"rank\": 3.222418103035778e-07, \"text\": \"Dublin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won theLeinster Chess Union's Armstrong Cup, Ireland's oldest team league competition (and one of the longest running leagues in the world), in 1926 and 1928.\", \"from\": 5287, \"to\": 5448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5306, \"end\": 5311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}, {\"begin\": 5312, \"end\": 5317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999990654796239, \"rank\": 5.428926360058791e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5320, \"end\": 5333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armstrong_Cup\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Armstrong Cup\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armstrong_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armstrong_Cup\"}, {\"begin\": 5335, \"end\": 5342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998197695648463, \"rank\": 0.00018026279511017772, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 1928 and 1932 Tailteann Chess competitions were won by John O'Hanlon.\", \"from\": 5449, \"to\": 5522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5477, \"end\": 5482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}, {\"begin\": 5508, \"end\": 5521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_O'Hanlon_(writer)\", \"score\": 0.9988828637097665, \"rank\": 0.0011152667627973456, \"text\": \"John O'Hanlon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_O'Hanlon_(writer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_O'Hanlon_(writer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tailteann Games ended in 1932, but O'Hanlon went on to win more chess competitions home and abroad, and was the first person to win nine Irish Chess Championships.\", \"from\": 5523, \"to\": 5690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5562, \"end\": 5570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\", \"score\": 0.6638756586635746, \"rank\": 0.48484848484842324, \"text\": \"O'Hanlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00d3_hAnluain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chess is still not part of the Olympic Games, but its world governing body was recognised in 1999 by the International Olympic Committee as a Global Sporting Organization.\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5692, \"end\": 5697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}, {\"begin\": 5797, \"end\": 5828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Chess Olympiad continues to pit the world's best players against each other.\", \"from\": 5864, \"to\": 5944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5868, \"end\": 5873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.303143276769843e-35, \"text\": \"Chess\", \"types\": [\"Q1914636\", \"Q11410\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chess\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over its almost 100-year history, there were some occasions when it was postponed due to major world events.\", \"from\": 5945, \"to\": 6053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a gap during 1939 and 1950 caused by the Second World War and it was held online in 2020 and 2021 due to the Covid pandemic.\", \"from\": 6054, \"to\": 6188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6173, \"end\": 6187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999999656474762, \"rank\": 3.435265799969167e-08, \"text\": \"Covid pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The45th Chess Olympiadis now underway in Budapest and Ireland currently has a team starting rank of 65th.\", \"from\": 6189, \"to\": 6294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6230, \"end\": 6238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 0.9999999988203854, \"rank\": 1.1794057668398534e-09, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}, {\"begin\": 6243, \"end\": 6250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998197695648463, \"rank\": 0.00018026279511017772, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"ht